<TITLE> HSC results on July 25 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)Results of the HSC and the equivalent exams will be published on July 25, said an official of the education ministry Wednesday. The information officer of the ministry, Subodh Chandra Dhali, told bdnews24.com results would be published on the website www.educationboardresults.gov.bd on the day. "We have proposed the ministry to publish the results by July 25 to 28. Now the ministry will decide the date," Prof Muhammad Shamsul Islam, chairman of the Dhaka Education Board and head of the inter-board committee, told bdnews24.com, A total of 618,308 students from the 10 boardseight general education boards, madrasa board and the technical education boardsat for the HSC and equivalent exams countrywide this year from April 16. Digitising the ministerial activities A press release from the ministry said in addition to results on the www.educationboardresults.gov.bd website, results would also be sent to a few institutions via e-mail this year as an experiment. The ministry said initiatives will also be taken to allow application online or via SMS for revising answer scripts. The applications must reach within seven days of publication result. Copies of permission for new institutions, including academic approval, permission to launch new subjects and departments, will also be available on the education ministry website. A pilot project to register students of all boards online could be launched by September through an Electronic-Student Information Form (E-SIF), the press release said. From now on, observation reports on the institutions under all the boards will also be available on the websites of the respective boards. These measures are being taken to speed up the activities of the education ministry and related departments, said the statement. bd
